<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <style>
        body {
            font: 14px/18px "HelveticaNeue", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            color: #000000;
        }
        
        h2 { color: #4DB8FF; }
    .auto-style2 {
		font-family: Arial;
	}
	.auto-style5 {
		font-size: medium;
		font-family: "Times New Roman";
		color: #4DB8FF;
	}
	.auto-style6 {
		font-size: small;
		font-family: "Times New Roman";
	}
	.auto-style7 {
		color: #4DB8FF;
	}
	.auto-style8 {
		text-decoration: none;
	}
    </style>
	
	    <script type="text/javascript">
     
    function toggle(id) {
      var e = document.getElementById(id);
     
      if (e.style.display == '')
        e.style.display = 'none';
      else
        e.style.display = '';
    }
     
    </script>

</head>
<body style="height: 344px">
<div id="secondary">
    <h2 class="auto-style2">User Creation Help!</h2>
    
    <p class="auto-style6">A User is someone who has access to the various functions given by the system.
        To create a user the following fields are required</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
		<p class="auto-style5">
		<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node1')" class="auto-style8">
		<span class="auto-style7">User Name</span></a></p>
		<dl id="node1" style="display:none">
			
			<p class="auto-style6">This is the name used to login to the system once the user is created.</p>
		
		</dl>
		</li>
		<li>
		<p class="auto-style5">
		<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node2')" class="auto-style8">
		<span class="auto-style7">Email Address</span></a></p>
		<dl  id="node2" style="display:none">
		
                    <p class="auto-style6">A valid e-mail Id to which the user has access.</p>
		
		</dl>
		</li>
		<li>
		<p class="auto-style5">
		<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node3')" class="auto-style8">
		<span class="auto-style7">First Name & Last Name</span></a></p>
		</li>
		<dl id="node3" style="display:none">
		
			<p class="auto-style6">These fields capture the First Name and the Last Name of the new User.</p>
		
		</dl>
                <li>
		<p class="auto-style5">
		<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node4')" class="auto-style8">
		<span class="auto-style7">Role</span></a></p>
		<dl id="node4" style="display:none">
			
                    <p class="auto-style6">A drop down which lets you select the type of role that you want to associate the user with. <ul class="auto-style6">
                        <li>Please check the "Create Role" help page for further details on types of Role.</li></ul></p>
		
		</dl>
		</li>
                <li>
		<p class="auto-style5">
		<a href="#" onclick="toggle('node5')" class="auto-style8">
		<span class="auto-style7">Submit</span></a></p>
		<dl id="node5" style="display:none">
			
                    <p class="auto-style6">Enter all the above mentioned fields and then click on submit. <ul class="auto-style6"><li>A new User with the given user name and role is created.</li> 
                        <li>A randomly generated password is sent to the corresponding e-mail address.</li></ul></p>
		
		</dl>
		</li>
	</ul>
    
</div>
    
</body>
</html>